      • unZip

        public static List<String> unZip(InputStream zip,
                                 String outputDirectory)
                          throws IOException
        Parameters:
        zip - stream of zipped bytes to explode into the given directory. Closed upon return.
        outputDirectory - destination of contents of zip. may be null, in which case '.' is assumed. If not null, then directory must already exist.
        Returns:
        the list of names/entries in the zip file in the order they appeared there.
        Throws:
        IOException

      • nextEntry

        public static FileZipper.EntryData nextEntry(ZipInputStream stream)
                                      throws IOException
        A helper method to get the filename and contents from the next entry. Use might be as follows: 
         InputStream is = ...
 ZipInputStream stream = new ZipInputStream(is);
 EntryData ed;
 while ((ed = nextEntry(stream)) != null) {
    String name = ed.entryName; 
    data = ed.entryContents; 
    ...
 }
        Parameters:
        stream -
        Returns:
        null when no more entries are available.
        Throws:
        IOException

      • finalizeZip

        public void finalizeZip()
                 throws IOException
        finalize the ZIP stream and its underlying stream, including closing the ZipOutputStream and thus the OutputStream that is being used by this instance. Once this is called, future calls to addFile(String, byte[]) will throw an exception.
        Throws:
        IOException
